00:09:17,639 --> 00:09:19,755
Play it again. Play it again.

161
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,431
Did he respond yet?

162
00:09:27,079 --> 00:09:28,194
No, not yet.

163
00:09:28,359 --> 00:09:30,748
Hmm. Maybe we shouldn't
have sunk to his level.

164
00:09:31,199 --> 00:09:32,314
It wasn't that bad.

165
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:33,919
Read it back one more time.

166
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:38,799
"My good sir, we are neither
crackpots nor wannabes.

167
00:09:38,999 --> 00:09:41,638
In fact, we are experts in our fields.

168
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:45,594
And while you hide behind your anonymity,
we stand behind our paper.

169
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,836
And later tonight, your mother."

170
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:55,998
-And you don't think that's too rough?
-We'rejust standing behind her.

171
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:59,438
It's not like we're gonna say
"boo" and scare her.

172
00:10:01,439 --> 00:10:03,953
How could you not tell us
you were in beauty pageants?

173
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:05,639
Because it's embarrassing.

174
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,956
Ha! It is. It truly is.

175
00:10:10,439 --> 00:10:13,636
Yeah, well, Amy writes
Little House on the Prairie fan fiction...

176
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:16,434
...about herself and posts it on the Internet.

177
00:10:18,719 --> 00:10:20,038


178
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:23,198
