179
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:25,231
Sorry. I had to get the spotlight off me.

180
00:10:25,439 --> 00:10:27,953
And tearing down women
is part of my pageant training.

181
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:30,511
Okay, we are reading that right now.

182
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,632
-Please don't.
-We got embarrassed tonight, come on.

183
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:36,434
-But it's personal.
-Why? Is it about you and Sheldon?

184
00:10:36,959 --> 00:10:38,358


185
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:42,271
-Oh, my God, it's about her and Sheldon.
-lt's not about me and Sheldon.

186
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:46,553
It's about a young woman
in the 18005 named Amelia...

187
00:10:46,759 --> 00:10:50,513
...and the time-traveling physicist
named Cooper she falls in love with.

188
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,472
-Oh, please show us?
-Please.

189
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:54,989
-No.
-Uh! You know I'm gonna read it either way.

190
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,189
Good luck finding it.

191
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,349
[SCOFFS]

192
00:10:57,519 --> 00:11:02,434
"Amelia and the time-trav--"
Found it. Ha, ha.

193
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:06,713
"It was just past dawn on the prairie
and like every morning...

194
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:08,751
